This is a mobile-first music and video streaming app with features for creators, listeners, and admins. It distributes ad revenue between creators (50%), listeners (10%), and admin (40%). Listeners earn when they engage with other creators’ content, but creators cannot earn listener rewards from their own uploads.

General Guidelines

Always design for mobile app UI/UX first (clean, modern, intuitive).

Support real-time updates for streams, views, likes, and earnings.

Ensure creators and listeners have separate but overlapping privileges:

Everyone starts as a listener.

To become a creator, user must fill out the Creator Form.

Creators keep listener privileges but cannot earn listener rewards from their own content.

Admin should have full privileges: dashboard access, ability to manage users, creators, content, payouts, and banner spaces.

The app must track referral codes and credit users accordingly.

Dynamic sections (Trending, Mix for you, New Releases, Must Watch and Wave albums) should always pull live uploaded content from the database and update automatically.

Use Supabase as the backend for auth, database, and real-time features.

Prioritize performance and scalability (handle large numbers of streams, uploads, and users).

Focus on making the design clean, modern, and user-friendly and Responsive for both mobile and tablet views. Keep the layout intuitive and easy to navigate. Prioritize good typography, spacing, and a visually appealing color palette using these color codes: #e6f7f1, #d9f3ea, #b0e6d4, #00ad74, #009c68, #008a5d, 008257.